                    <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/person/1111</idno>
                    <idno type="FIEY">21</idno>
                    <sex value="M" source="#bib1111-1">male</sex>
                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1111">In hagiography: Abraham the Penitent (or
            of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2614">Beth Sayyare</placeName>) was a monk
          from the family of <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/356">Awgin</persName> and <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/320">Abraham the
            Great</persName>. He founded a monastery at <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/1825">Zāwīṯā</placeName>, west
            of <placeName>Bamarne</placeName>.</note>
                    <event type="veneration" source="#bib1111-1">
                        <desc>The saint is venerated on last Friday of October in the East Syriac calendar.</desc>
                    </event>
